Grateful to NBC News and Zinhle Essamuah for holding space for survivor voices during this important conversation about the DOJ’s partial release of the files. So proud of my survivor sister and dear friend Dani Binthesky,  even in heavy moments, we still find ways to support each other and share some laughter together. These conversations matter, and so does who we get to stand beside while having them.

@DBinthesky 
@NBCNews 
@NBC

Trust in the justice system isn’t automatic for survivors, it has to be earned. Days like today make that painfully clear. Accountability matters. Transparency matters. Survivors matter.
Justice Delayed is Justice Denied. 

@itvnews 
@sharlenerochardofficial 

#releaseallthefiles #epsteinfilestransparencyact #transparency #matters #thetruthwillprevail

