Join us for an inspiring conversation where we blend spiritual wellness, fitness, and self-love. Host Sharlene Rochard welcomes Crystal Adell, founder of Black Women Do Workout, who shares a powerful spiritual message for the week. Special guest Kass Gray opens up about her journey in modeling, maintaining health, and staying true to herself in a challenging industry.

Discover practical tips on nutrition, fitness routines, and the importance of inner growth. We discuss the “platinum rule” of treating others as they wish to be treated, and how spiritual and physical wellness go hand in hand. 

Whether you’re on a fitness journey, seeking spiritual growth, or looking for motivation, this episode is for you. Stay positive, keep going, and remember: we come from a place of love, compassion, and tranquility.

